Interpretation:
  * All codecs operate per-decode-step in well under 1 ms.
  * A typical Qwen3-4B decode step on H200 is ~15-30 ms (bf16 forward),
    so codec overhead is <5 % of total decode latency at any op point.
  * v1.4 and TQ have comparable streaming latency (both are dominated
    by the Hadamard GEMM, not by the quantiser).
